[2] Russia (Astrachan City)
Date: Wed 13 Nov 2013
Source: Punkta [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://punkt-a.info/view_page/view/62125


Physicians, nurses, surgical staff, and patients at the Alexander and Mary Hospital in Astrachan are at risk of exposure to measles virus infection. As of today [13 Nov 2013], the building housing the Regional Surgery Clinic of the Alexander and Mary Hospital has been placed under quarantine. It is expected that the quarantine will last 21 days. According to the deputy chief physician, Dmitry Zakharov, 3 doctors and 4 non-medical staff of the Regional Surgical Unit are now confined in the Infectious Diseases Hospital with suspected measles virus infection. However, none of the 7 suspected cases have yet been confirmed by laboratory diagnosis.

There are about 100 bedridden patients under treatment in the Regional Surgery Department, and there have been no new admissions since 5 Nov 2013.

A total of 64 cases of measles have been recorded in the Astrachan Oblast (Region) since the beginning of the year [2013]. Previously, the outbreaks of infection have been reported among foreign students in the Astrakhan State Medical Academy, as well as in the Volga and Volodarsky districts.

--
